Governor Willie Obiano of Anambra State, on Saturday, disclosed that his wife, Mrs. Ebelechukwu Obiano, is to contest for Anambra North Senatorial District in the 2023 general elections. He said his wife is contesting the position to continue from her humanitarian services to the people of the state. The governor disclosed this while addressing members of Nigeria Union Journalists (NUJ), Anambra State chapter, at his home town, Aguleri, in Anambra East Local Government Area of the state, shortly after embarking on tour with members of NUJ to Anambra International Conference Centre (AICC) with 10,000 capacity, Awka City Stadium and the State International Passenger/Cargo Airport. Speaking further, the governor used the tour to inform the journalists that his administration had completeted a total of 133 roads across the 181 communities in the state and that International Flight will commence in Anambra Airport, in two weeks time. 